I enjoy doing things I don’t want to do because it gives me new perspective and I find it always comes with growth. You can’t grow without a lil struggle thrown in the mix, right?!

be your own motivation 🤭
.
Truly so proud of myself for how far I’ve come the last 3 years. I remember feeling so unhappy in my skin and would constantly say “f it” and overeat. I was barely getting in 2k steps a day, eating absolute garbage, and I just had enough of feeling bad for myself. I’m grateful to now have a healthy relationship with food and movement, but it wasn’t always easy.
.
Currently I make my health and fitness a priority and I make it a non negotiable to show up for myself in small ways every day. Fitness is not my whole life, but it’s a big part. If I can do it, anyone can 🫶🏼
.
#fitnesstransformation #bodytransformation #weightlifting #fitnessmotivation #fitnessjourney #beforeandafterweightloss #weightloss #fatloss #healthylifestyle

Daily habits that have changed my life | part 1
.
Let’s work on our habits together in the new year kkkk?? 🩵
.
10k steps a day- you don’t have to start with 10k right off the bat. If you’re super sedentary and aren’t used to walking a lot, start with 5k. Hit that every single day for a week. The next week, increase to 8k. The following week, increase to 10k. Rain or shine, I go for a walk and prioritize moving my body because the benefits are endless. My mental health has improved tremendously from walking more, and I’ve been able to stay in much better shape from walking more as well. (Your NEAT aka non exercise activity thermogenesis is how you burn majority of your calories in a day, which includes walking!)
.
Water intake- I’m telling you, a cup with a straw makes alllll the difference. Get a 40 oz cup or water bottle and try to fill it up 3x a day 🫶🏼 drinking water first thing in the morning before caffeine or food helps a ton!
.
#dailyhabits #healthyhabits #habitbuilding #changeyourlife #fitnessmotivation #wellnesstips #healthylifestyle

Daily habits that have changed my life | part 2
.
Going to the gym- we all start somewhere! I know a goal for a lot of people is to go to the gym regularly and prioritize their health/fitness. My top ways to hold yourself accountable are
▪️ plan your outfit the night before and wear something you feel comfortable in
▪️plan specific days/times that work with your schedule
▪️check off the days you go on paper or a whiteboard and have it somewhere you can see it
▪️good music to get in the zone and block out anxious feelings
▪️hire a trainer if you need structure/extra accountability!
.
Writing a daily to do list & intentions- my planner has quite literally changed my life and has made me so much more productive. It gives you a clear vision of what you need to get done and checking things off at the end of the day feels so good!
.
Here’s to better habits in 2024 👏🏼😊
.
